pact assessments (PIAs): Organizations must conduct PIAs to determine whether their processing activities have a significant impact on users' privacy rights and freedoms.\n8. Transparency: Organizations should provide clear and transparent information about their data collection, use, and sharing practices, as well as the choices users have in relation to their personal data.\n9. Data breach notification: Organizations must notify affected users of a data breach within 30 days of becoming aware of it, providing them with instructions on how to request further information or rectify any damage caused by the breach.\n10. User control and rights: Users should have control over their personal data at all times and be able to access, correct, delete, or object to processing of their personal data.\n\nThe IAB's Global Privacy Guide provides a comprehensive framework for organizations to manage their privacy policies and ensure that users' privacy rights are respected online. It encourages stakeholders to work together to promote user privacy and security in the digital economy."}, 'done_reason': 'stop', 'done': True, 'total_duration': 101106109247, 'load_duration': 1080073, 'prompt_eval_count': 1508, 'prompt_eval_duration': 5404770000, 'eval_count': 611, 'eval_duration': 95555917000}